    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound example featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six powerplant. The engine utilizes VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve, paired with a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle. Essential preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The suspension maintains its factory geometry with crisp turn-in provided by the hydraulic-assist rack-and-pinion steering. While the exterior and interior exhibit minor wear consistent with a well-driven enthusiast car, the drivetrain remains robust with no signs of bore scoring or AOS failure. It is a driver-focused machine with a limited-slip differential and staggered alloys, ready for immediate spirited use.",
      "price": 29900.0,
